cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.DS

This paper discusses a model-theoretic notion of specificity in artificial intelligence, particularly in non-monotonic reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with mathematical aspects, indicating that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses ordering and ranking, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
